   259→
   260→/* Sort the array currently in the stack. We do this to make the output
   261→ * of commands like KEYS or SMEMBERS something deterministic when called
   262→ * from Lua (to play well with AOf/replication).
   263→ *
   264→ * The array is sorted using table.sort itself, and assuming all the
   265→ * list elements are strings. */
   266→void luaSortArray(lua_State *lua) {
